{"questionId":"9069661","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>An organic compound, <strong>A</strong>, reacts with ethanoic acid to produce <strong>B</strong> using concentrated&nbsp;sulfuric acid as a catalyst.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/4e341b01fc9fcddd8a6251b84e80e8d5fe69e835.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Deduce the structural and empirical formulas of <strong>B</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/af6f141531c1fa4c2945f92f72c4446580bfe7bd.png\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>Structure:</em></p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/62e5c06567fa6d2ba85bde1b51e136e6f045a3cb.png\"></p>\n<p>ester functional group ✔</p>\n<p>rest of structure ✔</p>\n<p><br><em>Empirical Formula:</em></p>\n<p>C<sub>3</sub>H<sub>5</sub>O&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept condensed/skeletal formula.</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069661","referenceCode":"22N.2.sl.TZ0.a.i","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Deduce the structural and empirical formulas of B.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","1.2 The mole concept","Core","Topic 1: Stoichiometric relationships","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}